main event: Two round red objects were observed moving across the sky for 3 to 5 minutes in Lake City, Tennessee on November 6, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were described as being a little larger than a baseball.
The objects moved up and down during the 15-minute observation period.
The duration of the sighting was suggestive of an astronomical event, but no positional data was available for evaluation.
The conclusion states that no report was found in the file, indicating that the sighting remained unexplained.
The report notes that the description and duration of the flight suggest the objects were likely aircraft.
